<slide><h2>Increasing Interaction and Customization</h2>
<p> &nbsp;
</p>
<ul>
  <li> Many applications support <em>interaction</em> between users.
       <ul>
	 <li> user contributions
	      (e.g. <a href="http://www.linuxtoday.com/">Linux Today</a>)
	 </li>
	 <li> discussions
	      (e.g. <a href="http://slashdot.org/">Slashdot</a>)
	 </li>
	 <li> collaborative writing
	      (e.g. <a href="http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?WikiWikiWeb">Wiki Wiki
	      Web</a>) 
	 </li>
	 <li> form-based applications
	      (e.g. <a href="http://www.linux-firewall-tools.com/linux/">Linux
	      Firewall Tools</a>)
	 </li>
